  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Paralegal / Legal Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a detail-oriented and proactive Paralegal / Legal Executive to join our Private Wealth Practice team. The successful candidate will assist our lawyers with various <strong>private wealth and asset management matters</strong>, including legal research, document preparation, and translation.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in legal research, and document preparation.</li><li>Manage the document review process by coordinating comments from multiple sources and incorporating modifications under supervision.</li><li>Prepare preliminary and other basic deal documents.</li><li>Coordinate and manage document review processes by liaising with internal stakeholders, fund administrators, trustees, tax advisors and other professional parties, and consolidate comments and revisions.</li><li>Assist in cross-border matters involving Singapore, China and other jurisdictions, including translating legal documents and correspondence between English and Mandarin Chinese, where required.</li><li>Ensure confidentiality and adhere to ethical standards in all aspects of work.</li><li>Perform other duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Law or above; legal training and qualification preferred.</li><li>Minimum of two years of paralegal experience in a law firm or in-house legal department preferred.</li><li>Excellent organizational and communication skills.</li><li>Proficiency in English is required. Working proficiency in Mandarin is required to communicate with Mandarin-speaking stakeholders and review or translate basic Chinese-language materials.</li><li>Meticulous, able to multitask, and ensure transaction timelines are met.</li><li>Ownership-driven and proactive, able to manage matters independently and push projects forward.</li><li>Proficiency in MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.</li></ul>",
